<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>附件1：</strong>第三届“齐白石”大学生文化艺术节美术作品（中国画）展览参展申报表</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>附件2：</strong>第三届“齐白石”大学生文化艺术节美术作品（中国画）展览参展汇总表</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">(附件点击阅读原文即可下载，<strong>提取码：7e99</strong>）</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>第三届“齐白石”大学生文化艺术节全球征稿</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>（英文版）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Contributions Wanted for the 3rd Qi Baishi University Culture and Art Festival (Chinese Paintings)</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20200823/45b29646852e4cc0aa91bc7e29665e8f.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Focusing on the art pursuit and the cultivation of aesthetic taste of contemporary college students, Qi Baishi University Culture and Art Festival (Chinese Paintings) has received an overwhelming response since its opening in 2016. To inherit Qi Baishi's artistic spirit and promote China's outstanding traditional culture, the 3rd Qi Baishi University Culture and Art Festival (Chinese Paintings) will be held in 2020. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Contributions are wanted for this festival and details are as follow:</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>1. Theme:</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Euglogies: flawless beauty</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>2. Organization unit</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Guidance unit:</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Hunan Provincial Education Department</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Communist Youth League of Hunan Provincial Party Ccommittee</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Xiangtan Municipal People's Government</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Organizers:</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Hunan Artists Association</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Hunan University of Science and Technology(HNUST)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>3. Exhibition date</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">December 5th , 2020 ~ December 12th, 2020</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>4.Exhibition site</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Arts Building, Hunan University of Science and Technology</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>5.Scale of Exhibition</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">There will be a total of 100 pieces of works in this exhibition, including 5 special collection of works, 15 collection of works (including the special collection of works of "fighting the pandemic") and 80 selected works.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>6. Rewards</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1.For the 5 special collection of works, 20000 RMB will be paid for each work. For the 15 collection of works (including the special collection of works of "fighting the pandemic"), 10000 RMB will be paid for each work. The above mentioned works will be collected by HNUST. The 80 selected works will be returned to the authors within a month after the exhibition.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2.All the exhibition painters will be awarded with a published portfolio of this exhibition.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3.All the exhibition painters will be awarded with a certificate of collection or participation by the organization unit.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4.A certificate will be honored to the “outstanding organization unit” and “outstanding adviser”.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>7. Exhibition requirements </strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1.Painters must be on-campus undergraduates, postgraduates or doctoral students.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2.The contents of the works must be healthy and positive, and realistic works showing the fights against the pandemic of cronavirus are encouraged. The size can be 68*136cm or 96*178cm in vertical layout. Cooperative works and works in other sizes are rejected. Please do not mount the works as all selected works will be mounted by HNUST uniformly.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3.Preliminary evaluation: please provide an electronic file of the submitted works for preliminary evaluation (the image resolution shall be no less than 150ppi). Results will be published on the official website of this art festival (qbscfca.hnstu.cn ) and the official website of HNUST (www.hnust.edu.cn) on September 7, 2020. The organizing committee will inform the shortlisted authors by phone or email. Those who are not shortlisted will not be noticed and their submitted materials will not be returned.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4.Re-evaluation: the shortlisted authors should post the original works for re-evaluation as requested. All the original works will be returned at the expense of the organizing committee(including insurance fees).</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">5.All submitted works should be original works by the painter. It is strictly prohibited to submit works finished by others and imitated, plagiarized or duplicated works. Otherwise any legal disputes caused shall be on the authors and the exhibition qualification will be canceled.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>8. Requirements for submitting works</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>1.Submitting for preliminary evaluation: </strong>please send the Application Form and an electronic file of the submitted works for preliminary evaluation (the image resolution shall be no less than 150ppi) to qbscfca@hnust.edu.cn before September 1st, 2020. Please rename the works as “University name+Author name+Telephone+Title of the work”.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>2.Posting for Re-evaluation: </strong>please post the shortlisted original works before September 16th, 2020. All posted works should be well packaged and insuranced at your own expenses. The returning insurance will be corresponding to the insurance provided by the author. Insurance will be covered by the organizing committee during the exhibition. The organizing committee will promptly notify the authors of any damage caused during transportation due to improper packaging or disconnection, deformation or other problems caused by the instability of the works, but will not assume any responsibility.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Any changes to the author's information (especially the telephone number and detailed address) shall be promptly notified to the organizing committee. Otherwise, the author shall be responsible for the loss of his/her work caused. The organizing committee shall not assume any responsibility.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Postal address:</strong> Arts building, Hunan University of Science and Technology, Taoyuan road, Xiangtan, Hunan province, P.R.China</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Recipient: </strong>Guan Wei</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Tel:+86 18073268862</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Postcode：411201</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>9. Hosting rights</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">The organizers have the right to exhibit, research, photograph, video, publish and publicize the works on display. The authors who submit the works for participation and exhibition shall be deemed to have confirmed and abide by the provisions of this notice.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>10. Other Information</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Official website: </strong>qbscfca.hnust.cn</p>
